-- Spain Solar Industry Plans Court Battle on Subsidies, Economista Reports
-- Ben Sills
-- 2010-09-07T05:38:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-07/spain-solar-industry-plans-court-battle-on-subsidies-economista-reports.html

          
          
             Spanish solar power companies are
preparing to challenge the government in the country’s highest
court should officials impose a cut on the subsidies that
existing photovoltaic plants earn, El Economista reported. 
 The Photovoltaic Industry Association is working with KPMG on a
legal strategy which may include an appeal to the European Court
of Justice in Luxembourg as well as Spain’s Supreme Court, the
newspaper said, citing people at the association without naming
them.   
